def: Fitted to excite envy; capable of awakening an ardent desire toposses or to resemble.One of most enviable of human beings. Macaulay.-- En"vi*a*ble*ness, n.-- En"vi*a*bly, adv.
A ruddy eruption upon the nose caused by drinking ardentspirits; a grog blossom.
Firm; determined; fixed. "A most posed . . . and gravebehavior." [Obs.] Urquhart.
A plant of the genus Verbascum (V. Thapsus); the commonmullein. [Also high-taper and hag-taper.]
A special plate situated on the sides of the mesothorax andmetathorax of certain insects.
To make a dissonant, discordant noise one with another; to talkor chatter noisily. [R.] Daniel.
A cake made of the meal of Indian corn, wrapped in a coveringof husks or paper, and baked under the embers. [U.S.] Bartlett.
A light kind of helmet, with or without a visor, introducedduring the 15th century. [Written also salade.]Then he must have a sallet wherewith his head may be saved. Latimer.
